<!-- 04 — COMMON PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common Miele Failures in Los Angeles</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Miele appliances fail in predictable patterns — especially in LA's hard water environment. Here's what we see most often and what's actually causing it.</p>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌀 Washer Not Draining (F53)</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Drain pump blocked by limescale (hard water) or debris. The F53 error almost always looks like a pump fault but is frequently a limescale obstruction in the pump housing or drain hose. We clear the obstruction and descale the circuit before replacing parts.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">☕ Coffee Machine Not Making Coffee</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">In LA, the #1 cause is a scaled brew unit or blocked steam circuit from hard water — the auto-descaling cycle can't keep pace with 350 ppm water. Secondary causes: brew unit mechanical failure, grinder seized, or milk system blocked. We service the full coffee circuit.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🍽️ Dishwasher Not Cleaning</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Scale-coated heating element reduces wash temperature; blocked spray arm holes reduce water pressure; circulation pump partially impaired by debris. In hard-water LA kitchens, all three accumulate faster than in most cities. We test and address each.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌀 Loud Drum Noise (Washer)</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Drum bearing failure — the most common mechanical failure on older Miele W-series washers. The bearing produces a distinctive grinding or rumbling at spin speed. A worn bearing left running will eventually damage the drum shaft. We replace with Miele OEM bearings.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Steam Oven Not Making Steam</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Steam generator scaled with limescale — extremely common in LA. The scale insulates the heating element and eventually causes it to fail. We descale the generator, test the water inlet valve, and run a full steam verification. Annual descaling prevents this entirely.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🧺 Heat-Pump Dryer Takes Hours</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Condenser fins blocked with lint — the heat-pump condenser needs regular cleaning, which many owners don't know about. A fully blocked condenser can triple drying time and eventually trigger a thermal protection shutdown. Takes 30 minutes to clean properly.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

