<!-- 09 — FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">09 — FAQ</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Miele Repair FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How much does Miele appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Most Miele repairs run $175–$600. Drain pump replacement or door seal work is on the lower end. Drum bearing replacement or control board work runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed with repair. You'll receive a flat-rate written estimate before any work begins.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you repair Miele coffee machines?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — Miele CM and CVA series built-in coffee systems are one of our specialties. We repair the brew unit, milk system (CoolConnect, AutoSteam), grinder, steam circuit, and descaling system. This is a specialized repair that most general appliance companies decline. In LA, hard water scaling is the primary failure mode — we descale, clean, and recalibrate the full system.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Why does my Miele show an error code?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">In Los Angeles, hard water is behind most Miele error codes — particularly F53 (intake/drain) on dishwashers and washers, descale alerts on coffee machines and steam ovens, and F24 heating faults. LA water runs 250–400 ppm, far above Miele's threshold. We read the full fault history with Miele's diagnostic software to find the root cause, not just the current error.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is it worth repairing a Miele washer or dishwasher?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Almost always yes. Miele designs their washers and dishwashers to run 20 years / 10,000 cycles. A Miele W1 washing machine costs $1,800–$3,500 new. If your machine is under 15 years old and the repair is under 40% of replacement cost, repair is clearly the right call. We give you that honest number on-site.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How often should Miele appliances be serviced in LA?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Annual preventive maintenance is worthwhile in Los Angeles. Hard water scale accumulates in dishwashers, washing machines, coffee machines, and steam ovens faster here than in most US cities. Coastal homes also see accelerated wear on door seals and condenser components from marine air. An annual service call typically costs $145–$200 and prevents failures that cost $350+.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you use genuine Miele OEM parts?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes, always. Miele components are machined to tight tolerances — drum bearings, door seals, brew units, and control boards are model-specific. Generic substitutes rarely fit correctly and can void your remaining Miele warranty. We stock common Miele parts on every truck and source less common components within 1–2 business days.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Can you adjust my Miele's water softener for LA tap water?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes, and we do this on every service call. Most Miele dishwashers and washing machines have a built-in water softener that needs to be calibrated to your local water hardness — most owners don't know it exists. The factory default setting is usually too low for LA supply. We set it correctly through the service menu and show you the maintenance schedule that matches your actual water.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

